ive a genuine newbie an executioner's hood and 50 pp, and they're like &quot;oh, neat, thanks&quot;, but they don't understand.  I can give a long time EQ player 3 pp and a split-paw belt, and they're like &quot;Wow, I can parlay this into level 20 in 4 days&quot; (back before the level 10 patch, and when no one had anything much around here, in the good 'ole early days. . .laugh.  <br><br>Just a few thoughts. . .. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=salochin99>salochin99</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/29/02 8:55:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2209.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trivial loot code. friend or foe?</span><hr size=1> Loved TLC when it came in the warrens as i hate farming (don't want to buy stuff from a farmer that i could have got myself if they hadn't stopped me by perma-camping the mob).<br><br>It is a blunt instrument tho and it would be better if there was a separate TLC tag on items instead of Verant trying to use combinations of existing tags (LORE, MAGIC etc).<br><br>I half agree with the interaction argument but if i was doing a quest and couldn't find anyone to kill the green mob for me i'd be pretty fed up.<br><br>Nowadays I think the single char rule is the biggest factor in anti-farming cos I think most of the demand for twinking items is for alts and so no alts = less demand = less farming.  Therefore I think TLC is aless relevant on FV than other servers.<br><br>Overall I'm in favour but there should be a separate tag so verant had more precise control over what came under the TLC.<br><br>The recommended level thing would/will be great if/when it gets fully implemented.  Should of been there from the beginning IMO <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=farnoak>Farnoak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/29/02 9:09:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2209.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trivial loot code. friend or foe?</span><hr size=1> On the one hand, TLC makes it much harder for the farmers who perma camp zones for selling on EBay.<br><br>On the other hand, TLC is a hinderance to gaining equipment, which is quite frankly the cornerstone of this game.  The character advancement in this game is based entirely upon gear.  Everyone in the same class gets the same spells, the same skills, the same ablities.  The only way in which they differ is their gear.  TLC hinders your ability to get gear after a certain point in your character's development, therefore shutting down a major aspect of the game that Verant created in the first place.<br><br>I agree with the above poster who said that a major deterrent to farming is on char per account.  That not only severly restricts the total amount of characters that need to be equipped on the server (I'd be willing to bet that the average user on a blue server has 3 fully equipped characters, 2 of which rarely if ever get playtime but still need equipment), but it also depresses the demand for items which helps make things like EBay less profitable.<br><br>However, in a game called EverQUEST, I'd really like to see them make quest items exempt from TLC.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    The items that have been farmed the heaviest have historically been the straight gear drops, ie the rare drops from rare spawns.  Of course there's a few exceptions to this like the Ring of the Ancients, but for the most part things like the Molten Cloak, SMR, RMC, Yaks, FBSS, etc have received the heaviest farming.  In short, I think TLC was a good idea, but it was done way too broadly on this server.<br><br>Dungeons should be designed around TLC and existing dungeons should be gone through item by item with TLC in mind, IMO.<br><br>(Just one quick example of this...the final fight quest for the +int/+cha/+mana book in Ak'Anon involves killing 4 evil gnomes and looting 4 distinct pages from them.  Each separate gnome drops a particular page, so you can't just kill one and get all 4 pages eventually.  One of the 4 gnomes is light blue to a level 10.  Another one is yellow to a level 10.  The pages are MAGIC LORE but not no drop.  In order to clear the camp to get to the light blue gnome, you need to clear the rest of the gnomes which are all dark blue to yellow.  Basically it takes a group to do this quest, but if one person in the group is over level 12...TLC kicks in and the quest is absolutly uncompletable.  Get the MAGIC tag off an item like that.  It serves no purpose.)<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=farnoak>Farnoak</A> at: 6/29/02 9:14:16 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 678<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/29/02 9:36:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2209.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trivial loot code. friend or foe?</span><hr size=1> I think it was their only solution to the proposed lack of No Drop items that wasn't manhour-intensive when VI was working up this alternate rule set. Going through the entire item database and figuring out which items should be TLC'd and which shouldn't would have been a huge project - and a neverending one, since there would be constant tweaks to adjust for the fact that this thing is now used in a quest since the last patch, or people are now camping and farming this other thing for easy cash.<br><br>I also think there will be a different system in the next game... I do think that FV was a test case. I think they have watched how 1 character, no-drop, TLC and such played out here - both in the court of public opinion and in terms of server economy, frequency of eBaying, etc.<br><br>I view it as a necessary evil. A jarring disconnect in the fabric of the roleplay, an extreme annoyance at times, but far better than a massive swarm of campers.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ellywig</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>/shrug <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New Mod!</span><br>  Posts: 478<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/29/02 4:38:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2209.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trivial loot code. friend or foe?</span><hr size=1> Love TLC.<br><br>I think they need to tune a lot of items still (ie: Epic components shouldn't get TLC'd, nor should tradeskill components), but taken as a whole I really like it.<br><br>- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitl